    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-16T20:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-16T20:36:00-05:00" n="924"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d924">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2814.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-16T19:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1912—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Desperate condition in State of Durango, with conditions of anarchy throughout
                    and Durango City defenseless. I have made appropriate representations in this
                    connection in person, and am promised Federal troops. Saw the President this
                    morning; he informed me that he intended to abandon his policy of conciliation
                    and to exercise the utmost severity.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
